<br>
Is this reasonable to most mages? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/umissingruby.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MissingRuby</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#333333>(12/16/01 1:06:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=48.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   End game?</span><hr size=1> What level are we talking here, when you say end game? A monk has to be uber twinked to solo better (read more efficiant) than a mage after level 40 or so.<br>
I had a friend monk with fungi tunic and jade maces who stopped soloing around level 40. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uxushni.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xushni</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 86<br> <font color=#333333>(12/16/01 4:52:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=48.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.animationfactory.com/animations/people_m_z/wizard/wizard_raisehands_md_clr.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Where should mages rate in the soloing category..</span><hr size=1> No. you ever  try soloing LDCs and watch a monk solo LDCs and you will understnd, especially iksar monks. Most I know wear a high AC bp then get teh fungi on when they need regen. Also, they amosy never die, they FD. there HPs regen faster than our mana an They hit around the same as our pets, maybeless hp but they have 1200ac <p><img src=http://photos.netclubs.com/live/photos/photocenter/9/a/g/e/ge31rtf4brah3bpd0188nc11hc/sig.JPG></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/usarionmt.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SarionMT</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 315<br> <font color=#333333>(12/16/01 6:16:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=48.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Where should mages rate in the soloing category..</span><hr size=1> The thing is all of us on this board who are 60 solo relatively equally.  Equipment has little to do with how well we solo.  The one item that can turn a mob from unsoloable to soloable is our epic.  However, this isn't the case with monks.  They have to have the proper gear to solo.  And depending on what gear they have, they can solo differnet things.  One key item is a fungi tunic.  Another is their epic, so that they have spell and item haste.  One of our two primary pull monks has primal fistwraps and over (barely) 1600 ac.  With fungi tunic, iksar regen, and now the regen skill he can tear up the Grey with almost no down time.  However, thats not gonna be the case for every monk.  Also, they can fear kite.  Using instill doubt saves them a lot of damage, and time since they get to hit from the back.  Since most mobs in the Grey are in the 43-47 area, a level 60 monk can fear them pretty well, but can still fight them toe to toe if need be. <p>~~
